25/10/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Six people were injured when a bomb exploded near the entrance of a McDonald's restaurant in Trabzon on Sunday (24 October). A local police official said the authorities have ruled out terrorism. Authorities are looking for a man in his early 30s who was seen leaving the site before the blast. 
In other news, two Turkish soldiers were killed and four were injured when their vehicle ran over a remote-controlled mine in Diyarbakir on Saturday. Kurdish militants from KONGRA-GEL, formerly the Kurdistan Workers' Party, were blamed for the attack. (AFP, AP - 24/10/04 
